## Decisions Made
- Report entries grouped by PR author then PR number: Improves scannability by letting reviewers find their own contributions quickly
- List format over table for entries: Tables were hard to read with long IDs and descriptions; lists with `[type] id — description` pattern are more readable
- Report language inferred from agent directives: Eliminates need for explicit language config in workflow files; agent directives already reveal the team language
- Removed Source PR Details section: Redundant with the author-grouped accepted entries which already show PR numbers

## Problems Encountered
- English/Korean mixing in reports: Root cause was no language specification in template; agent translated headers but entry data stayed in source PR language. Resolved by adding language inference instruction.
- Multiple format iterations (flat list, table, nested list): User iterated through several formats before settling on author-grouped lists with bracketed type prefix. Resolved through iterative feedback.

## Constraints Identified
- curate-report parses entry IDs from PR body: Format changes to accepted entries must keep backtick-quoted IDs parseable by the curate-report skill

